                            <comment id="13263638" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 27 Apr 2012 13:14:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So for the compact case, this is a dupe of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3708&quot; title=&quot;Support &amp;quot;composite prefix&amp;quot; tombstones&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-3708&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-3708&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, it in fact requires a range tombstone (they could be millions of record having the &apos;abc&apos; and 2 as first components). The reason for the non-compact case is very similar, this amount internally to remove multiple columns. However in that second we could implement a workaround as we know which columns are defined for the table. However, for this too &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3708&quot; title=&quot;Support &amp;quot;composite prefix&amp;quot; tombstones&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-3708&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-3708&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; will offer a better fix, as it will be more efficient to have 1 (range) tombstone rather than n where n is the number of columns in the table and less special code once &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3708&quot; title=&quot;Support &amp;quot;composite prefix&amp;quot; tombstones&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-3708&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-3708&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is in.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So what I propose is for now to throw an error on the compact case and support the second one by deleting each column individually. Once &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3708&quot; title=&quot;Support &amp;quot;composite prefix&amp;quot; tombstones&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-3708&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-3708&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is in, we&apos;ll use it to replace the second part. Patch attached to do that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13402357" author="jbellis" created="Wed, 27 Jun 2012 16:56:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3708&quot; title=&quot;Support &amp;quot;composite prefix&amp;quot; tombstones&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-3708&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-3708&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; committed, is this still relevant?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13402970" author="slebresne" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2012 09:59:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It is relevant for the 1.1 branch (for which the patch is targeted) since &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-3708&quot; title=&quot;Support &amp;quot;composite prefix&amp;quot; tombstones&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-3708&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-3708&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is 1.2 only.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13403520" author="jbellis" created="Thu, 28 Jun 2012 22:16:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;nit: comment above &quot;cfDef.isComposite &amp;amp;&amp;amp; builder.componentCount() != 0&quot; needs to be updated&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13403766" author="slebresne" created="Fri, 29 Jun 2012 08:07:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed (fix comment fixed) to 1.1. Since it&apos;s not need for trunk I&apos;ve merge the commit but with &apos;-s ours&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
